==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bohea
<hw>Bo*hea"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Wu-i</ets>, pronounced by the Chinese <ets>bu-i</ets>, the name of
the hills where this kind of tea is grown.]</ety> <def>Bohea tea, an
inferior kind of black tea. See under <er>Tea</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name was formerly applied to superior kinds of black
tea, or to black tea in general.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bohemia</ent>⟦br⟧
